<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">BARBECUE SNACK MIX</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page050.article001.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY MARCY BLACK SIMPSON</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes about 18 cups </p><br/><p class="no-indent">To make these nibbles a little spicy, add 1/8 teaspoon ground red pepper. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">¼ cup butter, melted </p><p class="no-indent">3 tablespoons barbecue sauce </p><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce </p><p class="no-indent">2 tablespoons light corn syrup </p><p class="no-indent">1 (1-ounce) envelope ranch dressing mix </p><p class="no-indent">1 tablespoon smoked paprika </p><p class="no-indent">¼ teaspoon dry mustard </p><p class="no-indent">4 cups corn-and-rice cereal* </p><p class="no-indent">4 cups corn cereal squares* </p><p class="no-indent">3 cups bite-size Cheddar cheese crackers*</p><p class="no-indent">3 cups baked snack crackers* </p><p class="no-indent">3 cups pretzel twists </p><p class="no-indent">1 cup dry-roasted peanuts </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Preheat oven to 250°. In a small bowl, whisk together butter and next 6 ingredients. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a large roasting pan, combine cereals and remaining 4 ingredients. Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture, tossing to coat. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">3. Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes, until crispy. Spread in a single layer on wax paper to cool. Store in an airtight container for up to 1 week. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">*We used Crispix and Corn Chex cereals and Cheez-Its and Wheat Thins Original Crackers.</p><br/><p>______________________________</p><br/><p class="no-indent">WEB EXTRAS</p><br/><p class="no-indent">For instructions to make the Barbecue Snack Mix containers, visit cookingwithpauladeen.com and click on Web Extras.</p></div>
